		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Mar 30th 10:36 PM2004 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=16&mid=108042631280112&num=1&post=1&replyto=1080704045969928949"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1080704045969928949></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=320631"><span id=>TrollBerzerker</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />110 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=TrollBerzerker&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>lol... you played a warrior and tried to solo until 45? That's impossible to do with any melee class except beastlord and MAYBE SK (fear kiting) and ranger. Berserker is no exception. O.k., now to your questions..<br /><br />To number 2, berserkers can only use 2 handed slash weapons.. I think they also use 2 handed piercing on occasion. They also use throwing axes, which they craft through a spell-like ability of theirs. One component gets you 20 axes.<br /><br />To number 3, like I said it's going to be hard to solo to 45, but I can get you to at least 15. (NOTE: all of the following info assumes you have Ruins of Kunark, Shadows of Luclin, and most importantly, Planes of Power, and you're using a GOOD ALIGNED RACE) First, head to butcher block mountains and kill mainly dwarven skeletons. Collect their chips and give them to the dwarf in the paladin guild 4 at a time. This will get you lots of experience, some faction, a 2-handed sword if you're lucky, and some armor (if you're a dwarf and can wear the stuff). When you hit 5, which you should do rather rapidly, head to crushbone. Kill the orcs and get their belts for the quest, then leave when you're around 7 or 8. Head to Field of Bone using PoK and fight in the pit until you're 10 or 11. Then go into kurns and stay there until you're 15. Now you have to group.. go to paludal caverns and get a recondite group. <br /><br />(closing note, using the plan I just said, I got my froglok cleric from level 1 to level 20 in 3 days)</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Joo want axe?</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
